SIMPLE: uncloak
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncloak
<hw>Un*cloak"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>cloak</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove a cloak or
cover from; to deprive of a cloak or cover; to unmask; to
reveal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncloak</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncloak
<hw>Un*cloak"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To remove, or take off, one's
cloak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unclog</ent>⟦br⟧
